%% FMS Guardrails Orchestrator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant GS as Guardrails Server<br/>8033/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Orch as Orchestrator Core
    participant Chunker as Chunker Service<br/>gRPC (HTTP/2)
    participant DetIn as Detector Service<br/>(Input Detection)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant GenSrv as Generation Server<br/>(TGIS/NLP/vLLM)<br/>gRPC or HTTP
    participant DetOut as Detector Service<br/>(Output Detection)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP/HTTPS

    Note over Client,DetOut: Flow 1: Unary Classification with Text Generation

    Client->>GS: POST /api/v1/task/classification-with-text-generation<br/>TLS/mTLS (optional)
    GS->>Orch: Route request
    Orch->>Chunker: Chunk input text<br/>gRPC, TLS/mTLS (configurable)
    Chunker-->>Orch: Text chunks
    Orch->>DetIn: Detect on input chunks<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, TLS/mTLS (configurable)
    DetIn-->>Orch: Input detection results
    Orch->>GenSrv: Generate text<br/>gRPC/HTTP, TLS/mTLS (configurable)
    GenSrv-->>Orch: Generated text
    Orch->>DetOut: Detect on output text<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, TLS/mTLS (configurable)
    DetOut-->>Orch: Output detection results
    Orch-->>GS: Combined response
    GS-->>Client: JSON Response (generation + detections)

    Note over Client,DetOut: Flow 2: Standalone Content Detection

    Client->>GS: POST /api/v2/text/detection/content<br/>TLS/mTLS (optional)
    GS->>Orch: Route request
    Orch->>Chunker: Chunk input text<br/>gRPC
    Chunker-->>Orch: Text chunks
    Orch->>DetIn: Detect on content<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    DetIn-->>Orch: Detection results
    Orch-->>GS: Response
    GS-->>Client: JSON Detection Response

    Note over Client,DetOut: Flow 3: Chat Completions with Detection (OpenAI-compatible)

    Client->>GS: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>TLS/mTLS (optional)
    GS->>Orch: Route request
    Orch->>GenSrv: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/HTTPS to vLLM
    GenSrv-->>Orch: Chat completion (or SSE stream)
    Orch->>DetIn: Detect on output<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    DetIn-->>Orch: Detection results
    Orch-->>GS: Combined response
    GS-->>Client: JSON/SSE Response

    Note over Client,GS: Flow 4: Health Check

    Client->>GS: GET /health (port 8034)<br/>HTTP plaintext
    GS-->>Client: 200 OK (version info)
